1
00:01:51,590 --> 00:01:53,790
A while back, the bandit gang robbed a few wealthy households

2
00:01:54,510 --> 00:01:56,310
Including relatives of Commander Zhang

3
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:59,230
Now headquarters wants me to suppress bandits for the people

4
00:01:59,430 --> 00:02:00,230
Gentlemen

5
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,040
Do you have any brilliant ideas?

6
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,790
Actually, this bandit gang isn't that formidable

7
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:09,950
It's just that they've fled to

8
00:02:09,950 --> 00:02:11,680
the borders of Chen, Wei, and Liao to commit crimes

9
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,150
And are hiding deep in the mountains

10
00:02:13,710 --> 00:02:16,150
Suppressing bandits is a thankless job

11
00:02:16,710 --> 00:02:17,590
As the saying goes

12
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:20,840
When guns fire, it costs ten thousand taels of gold

13
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:23,000
It's simply using a cannon to shoot a fly

14
00:02:23,150 --> 00:02:24,080
It costs too much

15
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:25,280
I think since

16
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:26,960
we are suppressing bandits for the people

17
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:30,120
we should take from the people and use it for the people

18
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:32,000
Levying a bandit suppression tax

19
00:02:32,470 --> 00:02:33,310
is urgent

20
00:02:37,710 --> 00:02:39,590
This monthly vegetarian gratitude meal

21
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:42,470
is to let everyone remember the people's suffering

22
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:46,840
Even bandits know to rob the rich and give to the poor

23
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:48,400
Yet we're adding taxes

24
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:50,030
If it were you

25
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:51,750
would you choose to join the army

26
00:02:52,470 --> 00:02:53,430
or join the bandits?

27
00:03:20,710 --> 00:03:22,190
Eat slowly, don't choke

28
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:25,840
Commander

29
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:27,400
The Lucky General has arrived

30
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:28,560
He's finally here

31
00:03:28,870 --> 00:03:30,150
I haven't seen a shadow of him

32
00:03:39,590 --> 00:03:40,240
Commander

33
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:43,120
Could this be my last meal?

34
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:44,750
I didn't lie to you

35
00:03:44,750 --> 00:03:46,360
Everything I said is true

36
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,910
I've believed you all along

37
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:54,240
And I believe that Lucky General you mentioned

38
00:03:55,030 --> 00:03:56,750
really has skills

39
00:03:57,910 --> 00:03:59,630
He replaced Ma Laohu

40
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:02,520
He killed Ma Laohu

41
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:06,630
Come, let's have a drink

42
00:04:15,310 --> 00:04:16,080
Commander, I remember...

43
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:17,840
...you suppressed Ma Laohu before, didn't you?

44
00:04:19,520 --> 00:04:20,240
Yes, I did.

45
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:22,630
But not completely.

46
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:24,560
Ma Laohu ran rampant for years.

47
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:27,160
The people were terrified of him.

48
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:29,190
For a bandit gang to change so quickly...

49
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:30,680
...and win the people's hearts...

50
00:04:31,390 --> 00:04:33,190
...this bandit leader has some tricks up his sleeve.

51
00:04:33,510 --> 00:04:34,870
This Lucky General you mentioned...

52
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:36,950
...he absorbed Ma Laohu's men.

53
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:38,800
And formed a new force.

54
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:39,680
Called the Brotherhood.

55
00:04:39,830 --> 00:04:40,920
Flying the "Fan" banner.

56
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,600
Not only do they not rob the people...

57
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,040
...they distribute money and grain.

58
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:45,270
They are very popular.

59
00:04:45,510 --> 00:04:47,310
Many people have run off to join him.

60
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:48,750
He became a bandit?

61
00:04:49,830 --> 00:04:50,830
That seems unlikely.

62
00:04:51,390 --> 00:04:52,950
I specifically had someone investigate.

63
00:04:53,310 --> 00:04:54,800
He crossed the river from Weiyuan.

64
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:56,600
To run a hotpot business.

65
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,270
And offended Commander Qin.

66
00:04:58,480 --> 00:04:59,800
It matches what was in your report...

67
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:01,070
...pretty closely.

68
00:05:01,310 --> 00:05:02,120
Staff Officer Huo.

69
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:04,480
Is he the one...

70
00:05:04,750 --> 00:05:06,190
...who drove you to a dead end?

71
00:05:07,510 --> 00:05:08,160
Exactly.

72
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,000
So, what kind of person is he?

73
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:12,720
This man...

74
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,560
...he doesn't play by the rules.

75
00:05:15,270 --> 00:05:17,390
But he always has some dumb luck.

76
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,750
He looks a bit goofy and dumpy.

77
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,000
He is the type who...

78
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:24,560
...looks foolish but is sharp as a tack.

79
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,360
That's a talent.

80
00:05:27,950 --> 00:05:29,750
So I think...

81
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,560
...perhaps recruiting him...

82
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:33,190
...would be more useful than destroying him.

83
00:05:35,390 --> 00:05:37,310
Given your relationship with him...

84
00:05:37,950 --> 00:05:38,830
...will there be any issues?

85
00:05:39,510 --> 00:05:40,430
It's a sure thing.

86
00:05:41,310 --> 00:05:42,160
If...

87
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:44,190
...you go persuade him...

88
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:45,950
...to follow my lead...

89
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:47,190
...will that work?

90
00:05:47,510 --> 00:05:48,920
If it is indeed the same person...

91
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,310
...it's ninety percent sure.

92
00:05:50,510 --> 00:05:51,870
I want one hundred percent.

93
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:54,240
What if it's not the same person?

94
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:55,950
I don't care.

95
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,270
You owe me a Lucky General.

96
00:05:57,390 --> 00:05:58,600
I'll assume it's the same person.

97
00:05:58,870 --> 00:06:00,870
Staff Officer Huo is good at guessing my thoughts.

98
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:02,480
So...

99
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:04,630
...can you put aside your personal grudge?

100
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,830
Commander Chen's interests come first.

101
00:06:09,190 --> 00:06:10,600
It's just that this man...

102
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,560
...has a rebellious streak.

103
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,160
To subdue him...

104
00:06:14,390 --> 00:06:15,630
...I'm afraid it won't be that easy.

105
00:06:16,270 --> 00:06:17,160
It might...

106
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:20,950
...require a strategy like the Seven Captures of Meng Huo.

107
00:06:22,270 --> 00:06:23,360
Beat him into submission...

108
00:06:23,830 --> 00:06:24,510
...only then might it work.

109
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:27,510
Commander Qin.

110
00:06:28,310 --> 00:06:29,600
You've dealt with him before.

111
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:31,600
Do you agree with what I say?

112
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:34,040
Well...

113
00:06:34,830 --> 00:06:37,120
This man is indeed...

114
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:39,120
...very difficult to tame.

115
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,720
Suppressing bandits is an order from above.

116
00:06:42,190 --> 00:06:44,480
This operation for Commander Chen...

117
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,800
...in front of the superiors...

118
00:06:46,190 --> 00:06:47,560
...to establish prestige...

119
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:48,950
...is the best opportunity.

120
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:49,950
If we fight...

121
00:06:50,390 --> 00:06:52,120
...we need someone who knows him well.

122
00:06:52,630 --> 00:06:53,680
Know yourself and know your enemy...

123
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:55,870
...and you will never be defeated.

124
00:06:56,390 --> 00:06:57,240
Therefore...

125
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,720
Commander Qin and I...

126
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,510
...are willing to lead the troops.

127
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:01,560
For Commander Chen...

128
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:03,510
...to recruit this useful talent.

129
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:06,630
Good.

130
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:10,830
Yes, sir.

131
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:18,870
Nice, isn't it?

132
00:07:19,630 --> 00:07:21,070
Wait a sec, let me tell the Boss.

133
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:23,560
Win big.

134
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:26,830
Congratulations, Brother.

135
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:28,510
More and more people are coming up the mountain.

136
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,600
There's no room left to sleep.

137
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,950
I want to clear out the cave in the back.

138
00:07:32,950 --> 00:07:34,190
To settle these people down first.

139
00:07:34,870 --> 00:07:35,950
Okay, you arrange it.

140
00:07:35,950 --> 00:07:36,680
Alright.

141
00:07:37,070 --> 00:07:38,070
Follow me, follow me.

142
00:07:41,870 --> 00:07:42,870
Stop drinking.

143
00:07:43,310 --> 00:07:44,430
Drink some tea to sober up.

144
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:45,360
Okay.

145
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:52,000
Here.

146
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:02,800
Here.

147
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:10,510
Regiment Commander Qin.

148
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:12,950
Next time you should get a bigger sedan chair.

149
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,070
Otherwise, no one can tell...

150
00:08:14,070 --> 00:08:15,240
...who the commander-in-chief is.

151
00:08:15,630 --> 00:08:18,680
He's Division Commander Chen's favorite now.

152
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,480
We just have to obediently follow orders.

153
00:08:21,390 --> 00:08:22,510
Regiment Commander Qin.

154
00:08:22,510 --> 00:08:24,480
How can you say that?

155
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:26,560
I'm here to create an opportunity for you.

156
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:28,430
You're borrowing a knife to kill.

157
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:31,870
Yes, I want that guy named Fan dead.

158
00:08:32,270 --> 00:08:33,240
Don't you want that too?

159
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:36,270
He beat you until your head was bloody.

160
00:08:36,430 --> 00:08:37,720
The woman you had in your hands...

161
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:39,600
...was snatched right out of your bed by him.

162
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:41,240
Can you swallow that insult?

163
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:43,080
My own scores...

164
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:44,120
...I know how to settle them myself.

165
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,510
I don't need you to arrange things for me.

166
00:08:46,870 --> 00:08:48,390
I just want to remind you.

167
00:08:48,630 --> 00:08:51,550
You used to feed on the scraps from my chin.

168
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,870
Don't think about climbing over my head.

169
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:55,270
Regiment Commander Qin.

170
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:57,120
We have a common enemy.

171
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,550
We wear the same pair of pants.

172
00:08:58,670 --> 00:09:00,390
What's the need to distinguish high from low?

173
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,200
Well said.

174
00:09:02,390 --> 00:09:04,390
Then let me give you a piece of advice.

175
00:09:04,750 --> 00:09:07,960
The faster you climb, the harder you fall.

176
00:09:08,390 --> 00:09:09,080
Move faster.

177
00:09:10,790 --> 00:09:11,600
Staff Officer Huo.

178
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,550
It's safer to walk in the back.

179
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:15,510
Guns and cannons don't have eyes.

180
00:09:15,870 --> 00:09:18,000
We're hitting hard this time.

181
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:20,750
Wouldn't want to kill bandits but scare the Staff Officer...

182
00:09:20,910 --> 00:09:22,000
...that wouldn't be good.

183
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:24,200
Then I'll trouble you, Regiment Commander Qin.

184
00:09:27,550 --> 00:09:28,390
What?

185
00:09:28,630 --> 00:09:30,390
Brother Fan! Bad news! Fighting has started!

186
00:09:30,630 --> 00:09:32,360
Brother! The government troops are attacking!

187
00:09:32,670 --> 00:09:33,200
Go!

188
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:34,320
Go!

189
00:09:36,790 --> 00:09:37,360
Go!

190
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:13,790
Go!

191
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:14,910
Brother!

192
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:16,870
We can't hold them! Go!

193
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:17,870
Go!

194
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:20,630
Go!

195
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:21,840
Go!

196
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:28,200
Go!

197
00:10:29,270 --> 00:10:30,790
Brother, go!

198
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:00,510
Vicious bandits have appeared.

199
00:11:00,510 --> 00:11:02,840
Robbing homes, attacking merchant caravans.

200
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,670
Burning, killing, and looting.

201
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:06,910
To maintain public order...

202
00:11:06,910 --> 00:11:08,270
...our army has dispatched troops...

203
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:11,240
...to strike hard against the mountain bandits.

204
00:11:11,390 --> 00:11:13,080
The bandits are still on the run.

205
00:11:14,390 --> 00:11:16,270
They are armed...

206
00:11:16,550 --> 00:11:17,870
...and extremely dangerous.

207
00:11:21,030 --> 00:11:23,200
Looks like they're serious about suppressing bandits this time.

208
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:24,870
Fan Gezi's bandits...

209
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:26,120
...haven't done anything bad.

210
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:26,910
And they're still suppressing them?

211
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:28,840
They rob the rich, of course they'll be suppressed.

212
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:30,960
Officials and merchants are in cahoots, you know.

213
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:32,720
Looks like this time...

214
00:11:33,150 --> 00:11:34,080
...they might not get away.

215
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:50,960
They have Zhongjiang Hollow Noodles here too?

216
00:11:51,270 --> 00:11:51,910
Five bowls.

217
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:53,360
Keep it down.

218
00:11:54,270 --> 00:11:55,120
Bring us five bowls.

219
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:57,840
Gentlemen.

220
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:59,080
Sit inside, sit inside.

221
00:11:59,790 --> 00:12:01,480
Keep it down. Bring us five bowls.

222
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:04,150
Alright. Five bowls coming up.

223
00:12:14,670 --> 00:12:15,440
Three a bowl

224
00:12:16,390 --> 00:12:18,030
Five bowls, ten coppers

225
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:21,840
Pay up

226
00:12:25,120 --> 00:12:25,750
Pay up

227
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:31,720
Money

228
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,480
Did you bring any money?

229
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:38,240
Left in a rush, didn't bring any

230
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:41,000
No money, huh?

231
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:43,240
You trying to freeload?

232
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:45,630
Put it on my tab

233
00:12:46,270 --> 00:12:47,390
I'll bring you the money when I have it

234
00:12:47,630 --> 00:12:48,440
Who are you, anyway?

235
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:50,510
Why should I let you have a tab?

236
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:52,150
Pay me

237
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:54,120
You're not leaving until you pay

238
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,080
What?

239
00:12:55,870 --> 00:12:57,150
I'm running a small business here

240
00:12:57,510 --> 00:12:58,440
In broad daylight...

241
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:00,320
Are you worse than bandits?

242
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:02,030
Keep it down, keep it down

243
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:04,670
I am the bandit leader

244
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:05,840
You know that, right?

245
00:13:06,270 --> 00:13:07,910
I've done a lot of good deeds

246
00:13:08,910 --> 00:13:09,960
Who are you kidding?

247
00:13:10,150 --> 00:13:11,240
If you're the bandit leader

248
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,200
I'd give you my whole stall

249
00:13:13,510 --> 00:13:14,960
Everyone, come look!

250
00:13:15,150 --> 00:13:17,030
He claims he's the bandit leader!

251
00:13:17,030 --> 00:13:19,270
A bandit leader freeloading!

252
00:13:19,670 --> 00:13:20,510
Stop shouting

253
00:13:20,630 --> 00:13:21,550
Oh no, the soldiers are here

254
00:13:21,750 --> 00:13:22,550
Go, go, go. Move

255
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,080
You can't leave

256
00:13:24,630 --> 00:13:25,360
Let go

257
00:13:27,550 --> 00:13:28,000
Bandit!

258
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:29,510
Bandit leader!

259
00:13:29,510 --> 00:13:30,720
The bandit leader is freeloading!

260
00:13:35,910 --> 00:13:36,510
Over here

261
00:13:43,630 --> 00:13:44,030
Brother

262
00:13:44,270 --> 00:13:45,670
Did you see some men run past just now?

263
00:13:45,790 --> 00:13:47,080
No. Take this and search

264
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:49,750
Then they must be in here. Let's go

265
00:14:23,790 --> 00:14:25,440
Good

266
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:36,750
Xiaoqing

267
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:40,910
My Lady

268
00:14:46,510 --> 00:14:47,120
This way, this way

269
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:51,790
Trouble

270
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:53,150
Trouble, trouble, trouble

271
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:54,670
There's no back door

272
00:14:55,510 --> 00:14:56,120
Darn it

273
00:14:56,670 --> 00:14:58,440
They chase us around all day, running us ragged

274
00:14:58,670 --> 00:14:59,510
I've had enough

275
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:01,910
Let's just go out and fight them to the death

276
00:15:02,150 --> 00:15:03,390
Right, fight them to the death

277
00:15:03,790 --> 00:15:04,510
I support you

278
00:15:04,510 --> 00:15:05,600
Are you two idiots?

279
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:07,030
How can we fight with just a few of us?

280
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:07,630
Darn it

281
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:08,240
What?

282
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:13,360
It's all your fault

283
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:15,480
Ever since Yuzhen left

284
00:15:15,750 --> 00:15:16,840
You've been like a lost soul

285
00:15:17,390 --> 00:15:18,790
The brothers haven't touched guns in ages

286
00:15:18,790 --> 00:15:20,000
How can we win?

287
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:20,910
Master Wen

288
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:22,550
It really is you

289
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:24,200
Brother Fan, why are you here?

290
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:25,550
It's a long story

291
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,480
Those soldiers downstairs

292
00:15:27,870 --> 00:15:29,000
They're chasing you?

293
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:31,840
I want to use this precious place

294
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:33,030
To hide for a bit

295
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:33,790
All right

296
00:15:35,790 --> 00:15:37,720
Don't panic, we're performing "The Flooding of Golden Mountain"

297
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:39,510
You know it, just improvise

298
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:44,910
Later, go out the door and turn right

299
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:45,670
There's a river

300
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:46,870
You can swim out of Xinglong Town

301
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:47,840
Leading to Chengdu Prefecture

302
00:15:48,150 --> 00:15:48,630
Got it

303
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,510
Officers, what can I do for you?

304
00:15:52,510 --> 00:15:53,480
Catching wanted criminals

305
00:15:53,670 --> 00:15:55,550
We only have our troupe members here

306
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:57,270
How could there be wanted criminals?

307
00:15:57,750 --> 00:15:59,750
Come, if you want to search, go this way

308
00:15:59,870 --> 00:16:00,480
Take a look

309
00:16:00,550 --> 00:16:01,720
See if the person you want is here

310
00:16:02,390 --> 00:16:03,550
Look carefully

311
00:16:04,510 --> 00:16:05,240
Report, Captain

312
00:16:05,790 --> 00:16:07,960
Today is Mayor Wang's father-in-law's big birthday

313
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:09,030
He's down there watching the play

314
00:16:09,150 --> 00:16:10,150
We can't afford to offend him

315
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:11,960
Don't say *you* can't afford to offend him

316
00:16:12,390 --> 00:16:13,630
*I* can't afford to offend him either

317
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:15,630
If we can't offend him, why are you still standing there?

318
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:17,030
Withdraw

319
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:21,510
On stage, on stage

320
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:23,320
Hurry up, get on stage

321
00:16:23,840 --> 00:16:24,270
Okay

322
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:25,630
Quick, quick

323
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:28,030
Coming, coming, coming

324
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:51,870
Good

325
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:16,000
Master

326
00:17:17,070 --> 00:17:19,960
The water has flooded the mountain gate

327
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:21,270
Good

328
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:24,030
Good

329
00:17:46,310 --> 00:17:48,790
I'm going in

330
00:18:56,590 --> 00:18:58,000
I'll go down and take a look

331
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,160
It's too late, Brother, go quickly

332
00:19:00,680 --> 00:19:01,200
Go quickly

333
00:19:02,110 --> 00:19:03,480
It's too late, go

334
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:04,400
Go, hurry

335
00:20:29,270 --> 00:20:31,480
Stumbled and crawled all the way to Chengdu,

336
00:20:32,510 --> 00:20:34,030
living worse than a beggar.

337
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:37,510
Wanting to shed this bandit skin

338
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,550
isn't going to be that easy.

339
00:20:47,510 --> 00:20:48,590
Are you hungry?

340
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:49,240
Hungry.

341
00:20:49,510 --> 00:20:50,200
I wasn't asking you.

342
00:20:51,790 --> 00:20:53,030
Do you want to eat meat?

343
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:53,960
Yes.

344
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:54,550
Yes.

345
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:00,350
Follow me.

346
00:21:08,030 --> 00:21:08,590
Let's go, let's go.

347
00:21:08,590 --> 00:21:09,240
What's going on?

348
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:10,160
Get out, get out.

349
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:11,240
Get out, get out, get out.

350
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:12,000
Get out.

351
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:13,550
You don't even have money,

352
00:21:13,550 --> 00:21:14,550
yet you come here to scam a meal?

353
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:16,480
And pretend to be our boss's master.

354
00:21:16,550 --> 00:21:19,000
He really is the master of all your bosses.

355
00:21:20,030 --> 00:21:21,830
Then I'm your great-grandmaster.

356
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:22,400
You...

357
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:23,720
Fine, fine, fine.

358
00:21:24,110 --> 00:21:24,920
Say no more.

359
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:26,270
Xiugu.

360
00:21:26,960 --> 00:21:28,160
Let's prove it to him.

361
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:31,030
Eat him poor, eat him poor.

362
00:21:31,270 --> 00:21:32,880
Eat the boss out of house and home.

363
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:34,680
Eat him poor, eat him poor.

364
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:35,750
Eat the boss out of house and home.

365
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:36,270
Stop, stop, stop.

366
00:21:36,680 --> 00:21:38,720
Everyone in Chengdu knows this act.

367
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:39,510
Do another one.

368
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:41,510
Perform well and I'll give you a bite to eat.

369
00:21:41,590 --> 00:21:42,830
Can't you speak properly?

370
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:45,200
Believe it or not, I'll beat you up.

371
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:47,750
Let's go, let's go.

372
00:21:48,030 --> 00:21:53,720
Drive out the Japanese, defend Chengdu!

373
00:21:54,000 --> 00:22:05,510
Drive out the Japanese, defend Chengdu!

374
00:22:05,720 --> 00:22:08,880
Drive out the Japanese, defend Chengdu!

375
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:10,680
Compatriots!

376
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:12,110
Do not be deceived by the Japanese's

377
00:22:12,110 --> 00:22:13,310
sweet words.

378
00:22:14,110 --> 00:22:15,830
Today they open a consulate in Chengdu,

379
00:22:16,070 --> 00:22:18,310
tomorrow they can station troops in Chengdu.

380
00:22:18,790 --> 00:22:20,590
This is a naked act of aggression.

381
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:23,110
The Japanese invaders have already occupied our three Northeast provinces.

382
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:25,400
We cannot let them enter our Chengdu,

383
00:22:25,790 --> 00:22:26,790
our homeland.

384
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,350
We must defend it to the death!

385
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:30,920
Punish traitors severely, expel Japanese invaders!

386
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,480
Drive out the Japanese!

387
00:22:33,590 --> 00:22:35,510
The Japanese have made their way here.

388
00:22:35,640 --> 00:22:36,640
Compatriots, wake up!

389
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:37,680
Those few Japanese people

390
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:39,310
are currently at the Longxing Hotel.

391
00:22:39,550 --> 00:22:40,920
We must unite as one

392
00:22:41,030 --> 00:22:42,200
and stop their conspiracy.

393
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:43,920
Compatriots, come with me!

394
00:22:44,110 --> 00:22:46,750
Drive out the Japanese, defend Chengdu!

395
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:49,590
Drive out the Japanese, defend Chengdu!

396
00:22:49,790 --> 00:22:52,440
Drive out the Japanese, defend Chengdu!

397
00:22:52,550 --> 00:22:55,270
Drive out the Japanese, defend Chengdu!

398
00:22:55,550 --> 00:22:58,750
The Sichuanese don't seem very obedient.

399
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:00,510
They can't change anything.

400
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:04,070
As soon as the consulate location is confirmed,

401
00:23:04,790 --> 00:23:06,160
construction can start immediately.

402
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:09,000
Drive out the Japanese, defend Chengdu!

403
00:23:09,240 --> 00:23:12,160
Drive out the Japanese, defend Chengdu!

404
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:15,110
Drive out the Japanese, defend Chengdu!

405
00:23:15,270 --> 00:23:18,000
Drive out the Japanese, defend Chengdu!

406
00:23:18,310 --> 00:23:19,070
Compatriots!

407
00:23:19,550 --> 00:23:20,920
The Japanese are right here!

408
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:22,640
If you're a man, charge with me!

409
00:23:25,270 --> 00:23:27,000
Laoyao, you look after Xiugu.

410
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:28,030
We're going in.

411
00:23:37,550 --> 00:23:39,510
Get out here! Get out here!

412
00:23:39,590 --> 00:23:41,160
Get out here! Get out here!

413
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:41,920
Move aside!

414
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:44,680
Let's break the door down!

415
00:23:44,830 --> 00:23:45,350
Yeah!

416
00:23:45,350 --> 00:23:47,510
One, two, three!

417
00:23:54,030 --> 00:23:55,110
Don't you come any closer!

418
00:23:55,310 --> 00:23:56,640
This behavior of yours...

419
00:23:57,070 --> 00:23:58,750
...is completely destroying the peace!

420
00:23:58,920 --> 00:24:01,440
Your government wants to befriend us!

421
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:04,070
You are making trouble out of nothing!

422
00:24:04,480 --> 00:24:06,030
Please, all of you, leave! Get out!

423
00:24:06,030 --> 00:24:07,720
You're the ones who should get out!

424
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,960
Get out! Get out!

425
00:24:11,550 --> 00:24:12,440
What?

426
00:24:13,270 --> 00:24:15,310
Showing off your blade before Lord Guan?

427
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:17,480
Come on! Chop right here!

428
00:24:17,720 --> 00:24:18,400
Go ahead, chop!

429
00:24:18,550 --> 00:24:20,270
Come on! Come on!

430
00:24:24,720 --> 00:24:26,270
The Japanese jumped down!

431
00:24:29,750 --> 00:24:31,070
He jumped! He jumped!

432
00:24:31,350 --> 00:24:32,240
Scarface!

433
00:24:32,590 --> 00:24:33,270
Let's go!

434
00:24:33,550 --> 00:24:34,400
You Japanese...

435
00:24:36,350 --> 00:24:38,160
You'll never get away!

436
00:24:43,510 --> 00:24:44,830
What are you doing? What do you want?

437
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:48,240
Trespassing and rioting are felonies!

438
00:24:49,550 --> 00:24:50,400
Everyone...

439
00:24:51,240 --> 00:24:52,030
Break it up! Break it up!

440
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:53,480
Break it up!

441
00:24:54,750 --> 00:24:56,400
Move it, move it! Go, go!

442
00:24:56,750 --> 00:24:57,640
Break it up! Break it up!

443
00:24:57,920 --> 00:24:58,550
I'll kill you!

444
00:25:01,640 --> 00:25:02,240
Stop hitting him!

445
00:25:02,310 --> 00:25:03,480
You won't get away with murder!

446
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:04,200
Go!

447
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:10,550
Hit him! Hit him!

448
00:25:10,590 --> 00:25:11,550
Stop! Catch him!

449
00:25:14,310 --> 00:25:17,590
Kill him! Kill him! Kill him!

450
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:19,110
Stay away from me!

451
00:25:19,510 --> 00:25:20,750
I am your guest!

452
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:23,400
The Nanjing government invited me here!

453
00:25:23,680 --> 00:25:25,400
Invited you, my ass!

454
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:27,000
Invited you here...

455
00:25:27,480 --> 00:25:28,960
...to occupy our land?

456
00:25:29,550 --> 00:25:31,310
Kill him!

457
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:34,790
Kill him! Kill him!

458
00:26:09,310 --> 00:26:10,000
Are you alright?

459
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:13,070
Good! A hero!

460
00:26:13,440 --> 00:26:14,590
Hero!

461
00:26:14,790 --> 00:26:16,960
What? What? What's going on?

462
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:19,510
No gathering! No trouble-making!

463
00:26:24,160 --> 00:26:24,880
I'll say it one more time!

464
00:26:25,270 --> 00:26:26,960
No gathering! No trouble-making!

465
00:26:27,270 --> 00:26:27,790
Clear out, everyone!

466
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:29,240
Move along! Move along!

467
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:34,030
Why are you still standing there like a log?

468
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:36,480
Waiting for me to give you a medal?

469
00:26:36,640 --> 00:26:37,160
Hurry up and go!

470
00:26:37,480 --> 00:26:38,400
Alright, Officer. Let's go.

471
00:26:39,590 --> 00:26:40,160
Halt!

472
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:45,270
You killed him.

473
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:47,070
They can't leave.

474
00:26:47,720 --> 00:26:48,750
Who are you?

475
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:50,920
Don't obstruct police business.

476
00:26:51,240 --> 00:26:53,920
I am the Nanjing Government's Special Commissioner in Chengdu.

477
00:26:54,790 --> 00:26:56,480
Whoever lets the murderer go...

478
00:26:56,750 --> 00:26:58,000
...is guilty of the same crime!

479
00:27:02,680 --> 00:27:04,270
If the Commissioner hadn't reported it...

480
00:27:04,830 --> 00:27:06,720
...how long would you have kept it from me?

481
00:27:07,550 --> 00:27:08,270
Yes, yes, yes.

482
00:27:08,920 --> 00:27:11,000
I am investigating with all my effort.

483
00:27:12,160 --> 00:27:14,920
I've heard the Sichuan clique is full of infighting.

484
00:27:15,030 --> 00:27:16,110
And lax in management.

485
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:19,110
I didn't expect such a huge incident.

486
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:20,240
If you ask me...

487
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:22,400
...it's time for a cleanup.

488
00:27:23,350 --> 00:27:25,160
The Northeast fell first.

489
00:27:25,590 --> 00:27:27,200
The people of Chengdu...

490
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:28,590
...fear following in those footsteps.

491
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:32,030
Emotions are bound to be a bit high.

492
00:27:32,590 --> 00:27:35,160
At the time, the military and police acted together.

493
00:27:35,550 --> 00:27:37,960
And have controlled the situation.

494
00:27:39,070 --> 00:27:40,030
This matter...

495
00:27:40,720 --> 00:27:43,070
...concerns the relations between two nations.

496
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:47,000
You must provide a proper explanation.

497
00:28:17,510 --> 00:28:18,070
Hello.

498
00:28:18,440 --> 00:28:19,240
Is that Commander Liu?

499
00:28:20,750 --> 00:28:21,510
Let me tell you,

500
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:23,880
the folks over in Chengdu

501
00:28:24,110 --> 00:28:26,160
have real guts and temper.

502
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:28,350
It's pure Sichuan style.

503
00:28:29,400 --> 00:28:30,350
Commander Zhang,

504
00:28:30,920 --> 00:28:32,880
don't you come adding to the mess.

505
00:28:33,440 --> 00:28:34,110
It was a good kill.

506
00:28:34,750 --> 00:28:36,030
A damn good kill!

507
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:37,510
If I were there,

508
00:28:37,510 --> 00:28:39,270
I would've beaten him too.

509
00:28:40,880 --> 00:28:43,720
You're just watching the fire from safety.

510
00:28:43,720 --> 00:28:45,240
Easy for you to say.

511
00:28:46,680 --> 00:28:48,790
You've dominated Bashu for decades,

512
00:28:48,790 --> 00:28:50,790
what storms haven't you seen?

513
00:28:51,310 --> 00:28:52,790
Naturally, you can channel water to fight the fire.

514
00:28:53,310 --> 00:28:54,400
I'll put my words right here.

515
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,440
In the face of national righteousness,

516
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:57,590
whenever needed,

517
00:28:57,920 --> 00:29:00,510
I'm absolutely of one heart with Commander Liu.

518
00:29:03,070 --> 00:29:04,680
You son of a bitch, those words

519
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:06,480
actually sound pleasant to my ears.

520
00:29:13,310 --> 00:29:14,160
Mr. Tanaka.

521
00:29:14,510 --> 00:29:15,400
Where is Commander Liu?

522
00:29:15,680 --> 00:29:17,310
Our Commander Liu is really in a bad way.

523
00:29:17,680 --> 00:29:18,440
He can't make it today.

524
00:29:18,550 --> 00:29:19,510
He just went to the hospital.

525
00:29:20,720 --> 00:29:21,830
Yesterday he had diarrhea.

526
00:29:22,070 --> 00:29:23,070
Today he's hospitalized.

527
00:29:23,640 --> 00:29:25,750
Commander Liu is playing tricks.

528
00:29:25,880 --> 00:29:27,960
Commander Liu really did have diarrhea yesterday,

529
00:29:28,110 --> 00:29:29,270
which then caused gastroenteritis.

530
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:30,830
He also drank some unclean water,

531
00:29:31,270 --> 00:29:32,400
triggering his old ailment.

532
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:34,920
However, Commander Liu specifically instructed me

533
00:29:35,240 --> 00:29:36,790
to pass a message to Mr. Tanaka.

534
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:38,720
He hopes you will wait patiently.

535
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:40,070
Wait for three to five months,

536
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:41,750
when our Commander Liu recovers,

537
00:29:41,830 --> 00:29:43,030
he will certainly welcome you properly.

538
00:29:43,350 --> 00:29:44,750
Wait three to five months?

539
00:29:45,110 --> 00:29:45,960
My side demands

540
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:47,590
immediate and severe punishment for the murderer.

541
00:29:48,070 --> 00:29:50,640
But your government delays again and again.

542
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:52,160
It has already made the relations

543
00:29:52,590 --> 00:29:53,750
between our two countries very tense.

544
00:29:54,110 --> 00:29:56,070
If you don't provide a reasonable explanation,

545
00:29:56,590 --> 00:29:58,070
the consequences will be serious.

546
00:29:58,240 --> 00:29:59,070
Ambassador Tanaka,

547
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,110
compensation was paid, and the man was caught.

548
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:03,880
Exactly.

549
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:05,720
We have our own difficulties too.

550
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:08,030
Those bold unruly citizens

551
00:30:08,310 --> 00:30:10,440
incited the deceived commoners

552
00:30:10,750 --> 00:30:12,830
and smashed up our police station.

553
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:14,590
As the saying goes,

554
00:30:14,960 --> 00:30:17,590
water can carry a boat, but can also overturn it.

555
00:30:18,310 --> 00:30:20,310
If we don't control and appease the people,

556
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:23,240
how would we have time to handle your matter?

557
00:30:23,960 --> 00:30:24,680
Besides,

558
00:30:24,920 --> 00:30:27,310
hasn't the criminal already been locked up?

559
00:30:28,270 --> 00:30:30,160
During his illness, Commander Liu

560
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:31,880
has been constantly concerned about this.

561
00:30:32,510 --> 00:30:33,550
He reminded us repeatedly,

562
00:30:33,880 --> 00:30:35,070
since it concerns relations between the two countries,

563
00:30:35,310 --> 00:30:37,200
we must investigate the matter clearly.

564
00:30:37,880 --> 00:30:38,920
We are currently also

565
00:30:39,110 --> 00:30:40,920
worrying about finding eyewitnesses.

566
00:30:41,510 --> 00:30:42,920
We cannot let a bad person go,

567
00:30:43,270 --> 00:30:44,790
but we can't wrong a good person either.

568
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:46,270
Drive out the Japanese!

569
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:47,830
Release the anti-Japanese hero!

570
00:30:48,030 --> 00:30:49,000
Drive out the Japanese!

